- Add your file in assets folder. 
- include in theme.liquid file 
  i.e. 
  <!-- Your custom CSS -->
  {{ 'custom.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

  <!-- Your custom JS -->
  {{ 'custom.js' | asset_url | script_tag }}


EXAMPLE : 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  {{ content_for_header }}
  
  <!-- Default Shopify styles -->
  {{ 'base.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

  <!-- Your custom CSS -->
  {{ 'custom.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
</head>
<body>
  {{ content_for_layout }}

  <!-- Your custom JS -->
  {{ 'custom.js' | asset_url | script_tag }}
</body>
</html>



âœ¨ Using in Sections or Blocks Only

{% stylesheet %}
  .my-feature {
    background: var(--color-background);
  }
{% endstylesheet %}

{% javascript %}
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    console.log('My section is loaded!');
  });
{% endjavascript %}


ðŸŽ¯ Bonus: Inline vs External

Method	Use When
`{{ 'file.css' ->	asset_url
{% stylesheet %}...{% endstylesheet %}  ->	For section-specific styling
Inline <style>/<script> tags  ->	Only if necessary (usually not recommended for performance)

